s the Saxons and Caledonians. &sect; <HI>XXI.</HI> And re-e&s;tabli&s;hes the quiet and &s;ecurity of the Roman province. &sect; <HI>XXII.</HI> Gratian &s;ucceeds to the we&s;tern empire. &sect; <HI>XXIII.</HI> Maximus declared emperor in Britain. &sect; <HI>XXIV.</HI> Drains the province of its be&s;t men, and pa&s;&s;es over to the continent. &sect; <HI>XXV.</HI> Where he is vanqui&s;hed and put to death by order of Theodo&s;ius. &sect; <HI>XXVI.</HI> Stilico &s;ends Victorinus to command the Briti&s;h province. &sect; <HI>XXVII.</HI> The Britons choo&s;e emperors of their own. &sect; <HI>XXVIII.</HI> Con&s;tantine is routed by Sarus: turns prie&s;t, and is put to death by order of Honorius. &sect; <HI>XXIX.</HI> Aetius &s;ent into Britain; defeats the Picts and Scots. &sect; <HI>XXX.</HI> The Romans aban|don the i&s;land.</P>
