lexander, king of Scotland. &sect; <HI>LXXV.</HI> Exp$$ients to rai&s;e mo$ey. &sect; <HI>LXXVI.</HI> Is in&s;ulted by the earl of Leice&s;ter. &sect; <HI>LXXVII.</HI> Henry p$ep$res for an $xpedition to Guienne. &sect; <HI>LXXVIII.</HI> So|l$mn confirmation of the two chart$rs. &sect; <HI>LXXIX.</HI> Henry compromi&s;es his dif|$er$nce with the city of London. &sect; <HI>LXXX.</HI> Embarks at Port&s;mouth on an ex|pedition in$o Guienne. &sect; <HI>LXXXI.</HI> Marriage between prince Edward and Ele|an$r,
